Tarah Pettersen

About
With 15+ years in the field of design and 10+ of those years as an influential design leader at companies like lululemon, Amazon, Nordstrom, and Microsoft—I thrive when I’m creating an inspiring, inclusive workplace where talented people are empowered to be the best version of themselves, and motivated to deliver outstanding customer experiences and business results. 

My greatest value is my ability to cut through complexity and find the heart of the matter. I am obsessed with the customer and digging deep to understand the “why”, which allows me to see the bigger picture and connect the dots in new and inventive ways. I am not afraid to think differently, challenge the status quo, and drive ambiguous high visibility initiatives.

My passion is in defining an inspiring customer experience vision, and unifying and energizing teams around a common strategy that gives people clear focus and purpose. I believe that the experience customers have with a product on the “outside” is a direct result of how the organization functions on the “inside”.

Plus, I like to have fun. :-)

Specialties:
• Fosters a thriving creative culture, where team members feel supported, empowered, and happy to come to work.
• Attracts top UX talent and cultivates growth and career development that is focused on team members’ unique strengths.
• Relentless focus on—and vocal champion for—the customer.
• Strong command of user-centered design practices, visual design, and interaction design.
• Drives inclusion by working across multiple teams to gather diverse inputs and ensure all voices are heard in discussions and decisions.
• Inspiring, effective communicator who gains support and buy-in at all levels of the organization through research, data, and persuasive storytelling.
• Brings structure and clarity to work when faced with ambiguity by turning ideas into a clear vision and plan of action.

Greater Seattle Area

Laura Brandenburg, ACBA, CBAP (She/Her)

About
If you are looking to start a business analyst career, succeed in a new business analyst role, earn your business analysis certification, or even bring best practices and standards to your business analyst team, you are in the right place!

I’m Laura Brandenburg, Founder and CEO of Bridging the Gap and author of How to Start a Business Career. Our mission is to help you become a confident, sought-after business analyst with practical, real-world online training and certification.

Since 2008, I’ve helped thousands of professionals start and succeed in business analyst careers. I started my business analyst career back in 2003, after a few years as an editorial assistant (where I was bored out of my mind) and quality assurance engineer (where work got interesting).

My goal is to empower you to take charge of your career and become a confident, sought-after business analyst.

Our flagship offering is The Business Analyst Blueprint® certification program, where participants can earn their Applied Certification in Business Analysis™ (ACBA). The program includes:

>>>Foundational Business Analysis Skills: With practical, real-world online training, you’ll learn techniques and processes that elevate your career potential in any industry or type of project.

>>>Real-World Application that Builds Credible BA Experience: With hands-on instructor coaching and documentation reviews, you’ll create vetted work samples showcasing your experience while making an immediate positive impact on your current projects.

>>The ACBA Certification that Brings You Recognition: With a credential that documents your on-the-job application (no multiple choice exam required), you’ll be seen as an official and certified business analyst, which can open up new career opportunities within and beyond your current organization.

We run 2 public sessions each year Visit our website for information. We also offer private cohorts for teams. Get in touch with me directly for details.

For both individual BAs and BA teams, we also offer a variety of digital downloads and business analyst template toolkits to quickly support you in getting better results from your projects, and the BA Essentials Master Class which goes through our 8-step business analysis process framework to help you run your projects more effectively.

If you’d like to learn more visit our website at: http://www.bridging-the-gap.com.

In addition to our courses and templates, you’ll also find hundreds of articles and videos about business analysis and our free Quick Start to Success as a Business Analyst workshop.

My latest research titled ‘Do not fake it till you make it!’ is a synopsis of trending fake news detection methodologies on social media using deep learning, published in a world-renowned Springer book series.

Having graduated from the University of California, San Diego, with a Master’s degree in CS and an AI specialization, my journey is highlighted by a myriad of experiences from my brief stints at Facebook, the National Research Council Canada, and the Institute of Research & Development France involving data science, mathematical modeling, and software engineering.

I am an avid proponent of open-source and credit my career growth to this sphere of community development. I am also the proud recipient of multiple scholarships for my research and travels like Mitacs Globalink, Linux Foundation, Facebook GHC, ESUG, GHC India, etc. I currently lead the open-source and ML track for Anita Borg's IWiC group, co-lead the Women@ML BRG at Twitter, and serve as the Program Chair at PyBay.

Feel free to send a connection request!

You can also visit me online at https://jigyasa-grover.github.io/ or on Twitter (@jigyasa_grover).

Katrina O. (She/Her)

About
I caught fire coding. 

I always thought my dream was to be a proofreader for a little indie publishing company, sipping my cafe con leche and reading the opening lines to the next best-selling vampire novel. It seemed like an appropriate dream given my BA in English. I gravitated toward proofreading and quality control positions and even started my own proofreading business. But I kind of just felt meh. I yearned to learn more, yearned to learn something different.

And that's when it happened; the spark I was missing ignited the instant I clicked play on my first Python tutorial video. (I mean seriously, how could it not be great when it's named after Monty Python's Flying Circus?) Since then, I can't get enough. Web development calls to all my passions; it incorporates creativity and problem solving and I'm allowed to break it to improve the code (in a separate Git branch, of course).

I love applying responsive design principles and watching my web pages shrink into mobile screens and still look amazing. It's oddly satisfying. I think in a way I'm kind of like those web pages; I'm moldable, but I still keep my creative flare intact.

My specialties include quickly learning new skills and programming languages, problem solving, domain driven design, responsive design principles, website optimization, and the Model View View Model (MVVM) and Model View Controller (MVC) methods of organizing code. So far I have C#, .Net Framework, SQL, JavaScript, TypeScript, HTML, CSS, Angular, and Git/GitHub under my belt. I'm still enthusiastically grabbing onto any other programming languages, frameworks, or principles I can integrate into the coding web in my head.

About
Marketing specialist with analytical expertise who uses data science techniques to solve complex business problems. Recently graduated with an M.S. in Marketing Analytics.

From Seattle to San Francisco to Dubai, I’ve used my marketing analytic skills to help diverse tech/PR companies understand consumer behavior through market research. Since many of these companies were fast-growing startups, my projects were self-driven. They required flexibility and decisiveness by leveraging data. Some of my responsibilities included conducting market research, running UX interviews, and A/B testing ad creatives through social media campaigns.

Prior to marketing, I explored a career in public policy. The public sector helped me identify my three biggest strengths:
1) Finding trends in patterns and identifying consumer perceptions and opinions. The most pressing issues for citizens are comparable to customer-focused pain points.
2) Having research-driven and data-backed solutions are key to creating strong outcomes.
3) Communicating with diverse teammates and stakeholders is essential. Sometimes nobody in the room has an answer, so the best thing to do is to leave the room and find those who do.

The lessons I gained led me to pursue my M.S. in Marketing Analytics and fueled my ambition: to add value by helping teams produce and market products that are meaningful, enjoyable, and effective.

I am passionate about marketing and am always seeking new opportunities to explore, learn, and grow.

Interests/Specialties: Marketing Strategy | Product Marketing | Data Analytics | Customer Analytics | Marketing Research | Digital Marketing & Advertising | Social Media Marketing | Consulting

Technical Skills: R, SAS, SQL, Python, Tableau

Umang Arora (She/Her)

About
Design for me is creating or giving form to a kaleidoscope of emotions, which are in turn felt by the different senses of the user and thus giving the best possible user experience.

In my 6 years of experience as a UI/UX Designer, I have learned to manage multiple projects, work in tight schedules, present novel designs and concepts to top stakeholders. My strength lies in maintaining a collaborative environment and open communication with all team members.

Currently working as a Product Designer at Uplift. Graduated Masters in Information Experience Design (with distinction) from Pratt Institute, New York. Skilled in UI Design; UX Design, Research, Testing; Mobile Application Design; Conversational UX (VUX and VUI); Design Strategies; Data Analysis. With a keen interest in photography, dance, music, and arts, I believe in weaving aesthetics into our lives to make it more beautiful and satisfying.

In fact, my first impression of good design comes from the wheel and how a simple aesthetic translates into such a multitude of functionalities. The wheel is one of the key components in every aspect of life. It’s like a building block, a single piece which is perfect in itself yet if you add another one it doesn’t lose its design aesthetic. My journey with design has centred around minimalistic aesthetics without losing functionality.

Location
New York, New York, United States

Priyanka Parmar (She/Her)

About
I strive to make things simple by emphasizing the roots and designing apps that people can easily use. I am passionate about finding ways to solve a problem, observing human behavior, understanding psychology, and being full of creative ideas. 

I create intuitive and beautiful user experiences from conception to implementation, while constantly challenging myself and learning new skills in research and user experience. I have worked on several different projects and delivered great user experiences. For a glimpse:

One complex project was B2B and for a Germany-based client, the requirement was pretty hard to implement as it was based on a database maintained by the client throughout his 15 years of career. The data was pretty huge. I understood and analyzed the data and normalized it into various categories. I generated easy & intuitive user flows that the client liked and decided to kick start the implementation.

I also have experience in B2C projects where one project was about preparing for competitive exams. Similar to many other projects, I planned and executed UX research. I prepared and shared the survey questionnaire with 250+ prospective users. The survey included subjective questions to have a deep understanding of user requirements. I analyzed the responses and then designed the features with priority. The mobile app was a success in its very first launch.

I also revamped many web apps, for one project I converted 108 pages website into 8 pages website by improving the workflows & information architecture which led to a simplified user experience.

To know more about my work leave a message and also check out my Behance portfolio.

About
Early in my career, I was asked about my definition of a great product and how I would approach product management to create great products. My answer was – A good product motivates consumers to use it, and as a product manager, my goal would be to understand what motivates the consumers of my product.

After 10+ years of leading product teams in the telecom, hospitality, revenue management, and retail eCommerce industries, I have realized that good product leaders inspire their teams to create products that consumers love to use.

I lead a product team at Lowes that owns a portfolio of strategic platform products in my current role.

As a servant leader, my focus is always towards:

➤ Mentoring and growing individuals to take on more significant challenges.
➤ Developing results-oriented, customer-focused teams.
➤ Fostering a culture of grass-root innovation based on validated learning.
➤ Building a vision and strategy that is backed by data-driven decision-making.

I have an MBA in Technology Strategy from the Georgia Institute of Technology and a BS in computer science.

My journey has helped me build a broad perspective about leading cross-functional teams that solve challenging customer problems with great products.

About
Achiever computer scientist and engineer with 10+ years of experience in design, development and deployment of big data systems and scalable machine learning applications. Extensive experience on software implementation; Quick learner and enthusiastic to tackle new challenges. Excited to leveling up businesses' strength to superb by applying data-driven and machine learning solutions.

Currently I am working in Intuit focusing on developing AI and ML application in the field of risk and fraud.

At Western Michigan University as part of my doctoral research, I have worked on a range of projects including Semi-supervised deep reinforcement learning for IoT applications, IoT big data and streaming data analytics using deep learning, Integration of Horizontal IoT Services, High level descriptive language for Software Define Network policies, and Cloud Resource Provisioning by Online Auction algorithms to support IoT applications. These works were published in prestigious journals and conferences and have drawn the attention of researchers worldwide. Also I received the IEEE ComSoc 2018 Best Survey Paper Award for my paper "Internet of Things: A survey on Enabling Technologies, Protocols, and Applications" published in IEEE Communications Surveys and Tutorials, Volume 17, No. 4.

My specialties and interests include:
- Deep Learning (CNN, RNN, LSTM, etc.), Reinforcement Learning, Machine Learning algorithms (supervised, semi-supervised, and unsupervised).
- Internet of Things technologies, IoT Smart Services, IoT data streaming analytics.

About
I'm passionate about technology that solves real problems, with a knack for algorithmic, optimization, or machine learning challenges, proven to perform under pressure. I have a heavy background in algorithms & data structures, and machine learning, worked at Coinbase, Twitter, Facebook, Google, and IBM research, and won or made the onsite final at some of the biggest programming contests in the world, like Google Code Jam or TopCoder Open.

Most recently, I was the first ML Engineer at Coinbase, acting as the team's tech lead for the last three years over a 40+ team. I had a role in building, designing, or advising every ML model running in production currently at Coinbase, as well as the technical and strategic direction. Highlights:

Landed double-digit increases in site-wide net revenue and engagement across the Feed, Growth & Notifications, and user spend limits;
Created Auto-ML-like lego-blocks around tabular data, sequence & text data (using Transformers of ChatGPT fame & deep learning), and support for blending these models to help 10x the team;
Set long-term technical direction for the team, owned large parts of the interview process, published a blog post around our stack, contributed to a KDD presentation, and ran a knowledge-sharing group and boot camp;
Worked on the first web3 use cases.

I was a founding engineer at Memo.ai (acquired by Coinbase) working on various NLP tasks. Previously, I did big data work at BitDefender and got my first industry experience through internships at Google (2008), Facebook (2010), and Twitter (2012).

Published several theoretical computer science papers in string algorithms and strand detection, with an h-index of 4.

I also built the first real-time turnout electoral map for the Romanian parliamentary elections, used by more than 1% of the Romanian voting population.

I have Research Master's degree in Computer Science from the University of Maryland, College Park, under Prof. Mohammad HajiAghayi and a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science from the University of Bucharest, Faculty of Mathematics and Informatics.
